PGP key not yet generated.

This URL (`/.well-known/pgp-key.asc`) is referenced by `SECURITY.md` §17 as
the canonical fingerprint distribution endpoint for contacto@praeventio.net
when reporters want to encrypt vulnerability reports end-to-end.

NOTE 2026-05-19: Step-by-step generation procedure documented at
`docs/security/PGP_GENERATION.md` (offline RSA 4096 + 2-year expiry +
private key vault). Bloqueado por input usuario.

The placeholder is committed deliberately so the URL returns 200 (rather
than a 404 that an attacker could intercept and replace with a key they
control via a CDN MITM). It should be replaced with a real ASCII-armored
public key the moment the security lead generates one.

PROCEDURE TO REPLACE
====================
Ver `docs/security/PGP_GENERATION.md` para el procedimiento completo
incluyendo: generación offline, export ASCII-armored, vault de private
key, descomenta `Encryption:` en security.txt, verificación post-deploy
con `gpg --import-options show-only`, política de rotación 24 meses,
revocación si compromiso.

Resumen ultracorto (ver doc completo):
1. Security lead generates an offline GPG keypair on an air-gapped machine:
     gpg --quick-generate-key "Praeventio Guard Security <contacto@praeventio.net>" rsa4096 sign,encr 2y
   (alternativa: `gpg --full-generate-key` para Curve25519 / RSA 4096-bit
   con expiry custom)
2. Export the public key:
     gpg --armor --export contacto@praeventio.net > public/.well-known/pgp-key.asc
3. Replace this file with the exported `pgp-key.asc`.
4. Publish the fingerprint in `SECURITY.md` §17 and on the public website's
   `/.well-known/security.txt` `Encryption:` line:
     sed -i 's|^# Encryption:|Encryption:|' public/.well-known/security.txt
5. Sign the next git tag (`v1.x.y`) with the key so reporters can verify the
   chain: `git tag -s v1.x.y -m "release"`.
6. Backup private key a vault offline (NUNCA al repo).
7. Open a PR titled `security: rotate PGP key (fp <new-fingerprint>)` so the
   rotation event is auditable.

DO NOT delete this placeholder before the real key is uploaded — the
404 → silent-failure path is the worst outcome for a vuln reporter.

